198650.「さすがは <cs_pchero>君。\n キミならば なんの問題もなく\n こ:
Bravo, <cs_pchero>.
I knew you'd have no issues finding your
way here.

198652.「……おっと。これは すまん。\n いろいろ 説明が まだだったな。:
...Oh. My apologies. I suppose I should
explain everything to you.

198653.「この世には キミたちの知らない\n 未知の次元が 無数に存在し そこには\n:
In this world, there exist countless dimensions hidden from sight, and within them dwell beings with supernatural
abilities...

198654.「そして 時間や空間をも超える 彼らを\n 監視 あるいは 排除するために\n:
Thus, there is an organization that was created for the purpose of monitoring them or even eliminating them. Even those who
transcend time and space.

198655.「時空監察機関ケイブ……。\n その アストルティアでの活動拠点が\n 何を隠そ:
The Spacetime Surveillance Agency Cave...
Their base of operations in Astoltia, believe
it or not, is right here.

198656.「キミたちが パクレ警部として知る\n ワガハイの今の姿も この世界で活動するた:
The one you know as Inspector Pakul is merely
a cover that I use to do my duties in this
world...

198657.「高次元エージェント\n コードナンバー Ｐ８９０！: High Dimensional Agent, Code Number P890!

198658.「これこそが ワガハイの真の姿なのだ！！: THIS is what I truly am!!

198659.「銀の丘の扉……。フォステイル……。\n ゴブル砂漠東に落ちた 半球状物質……。:
The door in Silver Hill... Fostail...
The strange spherical objects in the eastern
Goble Desert...

198660.「この世界の領分を超えた存在が 現れしときこそ\n ワガハイの出番！:
When an unexplainable phenomenon appears in
this world, that is when I come forth!

198661.「彼らの過剰な干渉が 害をもたらさぬよう\n ワガハイたち エージェントが\n:
My fellow agents and I monitor these
occurrences on a daily basis, to ensure that
their excessive interference causes no harm!

198662.「ここ最近 キミの見てきた事件も例外ではない。\n 詳細は まだ 語れないがな…:
The cases you have been a part of are no
exception. I can't go into the finer details
just yet, but...

198663.「……さて。本題に 入ろうか。\n キミを ここへ呼んだ理由は\n 木箱のメッセ:
...I'll cut right to the chase, then. The
reason I had you come here was as stated
in the message inside the crate.

198664.「アストルティアでの キミの活躍。\n とても すばらしいものだった。\n ワガ:
Your work in Astoltia is quite commendable.
I can see an extraordinary talent within you.

198665.「<cs_pchero>君！\n キミも 高次元エージェントとして\n ワガハイ:
<cs_pchero>! How would you like to
work alongside me as a High Dimensional
Agent?!

198666.「特別任務・第８９０号により\n ワガハイは 有能な人材を ケイブに\n スカウ:
Special Mission No. 890 grants me
authorization to scout qualifying candidates
for the Cave.

198667.「時空監察機関ケイブは 福利厚生も充実！\n 有給休暇 季節休暇も 多数あり！\:
The Cave offers a full range of benefits!
Paid vacation, seasonal leave...and more!
Not to mention, you are paid daily!

198668.「さらに 今なら 特殊任務ツールを\n 無料プレゼント中！！:
And that's not all! Right now, we are giving
away a FREE Special Mission Tool!

198670.「わあっ やっぱり パクレ警部は\n ボクの思ったとおり すごいヒトだったんだね:
Wow! You're just as amazing as I thought,
Inspector Pakul!

198671.「ほう……。\n <cs_pchero>君に 気づかれずに\n 後を つけてきた:
So... It seems you managed to follow
<cs_pchero> here without being detected...

198672.「弟子入りの話ならば 断ったはずだが？\n 直談判でも するつもりかね？:
I believe I already declined your request for
apprenticeship. Have you come to appeal to
me directly?

198673.「……それとも\n ワガハイの命を 取りにきたのかね？: ...or have you come to take my life?

198674.「……あははっ！\n やっぱり 最初から わかってたんだ。:
Ahaha...!
I knew it all along.

198675.「そこのアストルティア原住民のおかげで\n ここを 突き止めることが できました:
Thanks to our native of Astoltia here, I was
able to locate this place. A fitting place for
you to die, wouldn't you say?

198676.「イレイザーＧｅ５０……。\n それが あなたに 引導を渡す者の名です。:
Eraser GE50...
The name of the one who shall lead you.

198677.「高次元エージェント Ｐ８９０。\n 今こそ あなたの命を いただきましょう！！:
High Dimensional Agent P890...
Your life ends here!

198678.「イレイザーシリーズの暗殺者を 寄こすか。\n ワガハイも 出世したものだ。:
So they've sent an Eraser-series assassin, I
see... I must say. You've come quite a long
way to get here.

198679.「……やはり 死の道化の異名を持つ あなたを\n たやすく しとめることは でき:
Indeed... It appears that taking down the one
known as the Buffoon of Death will be no
simple feat...

198680.「ならば そこのアストルティア原住民を捕らえ\n 人質として 利用させてもらうと:
Then I shall capture the Astoltian native and
hold them as my hostage.

198681.「それは 困るな。\n こちらが 先に スカウト中なのだよ。:
Just one tiny problem with that, you see.
I was just about to scout them.

198682.「<cs_pchero>君。\n こいつは キミだけで 戦うには\n すこしばか:
<cs_pchero>. This one is a bit tough
if you intend to fight alone.

198683.「返事をもらう前だが ここはひとつ\n ワガハイと共闘と シャレ込んでみないかね:
I know you've yet to reply to my offer, how
about we join forces for the time being?

198684.「ほほう そう来ますか。\n ならば まとめて その息の根を\n 止めてさしあげ:
Oh, ho...so that's how it is, is it?
Then I'll just have to choke the life out of
you both!!

198685.「……おっと。\n 相談している時間は くれないようだ。\n 行くぞ <cs_p:
...Rats. It appears we have no time to
discuss a strategy. Let's do this!

198686.「……ふむ。よくやった <cs_pchero>君。\n 思ったとおり なかなかの:
...Yes. Well done, <cs_pchero>.
As expected, you're quite skilled.

198688.「まだだっ！\n 私は まだ 戦えますっ！！:
This isn't over yet!
I can still fight!!

198689.「これで 終わりでは ありませんよ……。\n 第２ 第３の刺客……が…………。:
This is not the end...
There will be a second assassin...
Even a third assassin...will...

198691.「……やれやれ。人気者は つらいな。: Oh, dear... It's not easy being so popular.

198692.「まあ エージェントにとって\n このようなことは 日常茶飯事だがね。:
Well, for an Agent like me... This sort of
thing happens every day.

198693.「……さて <cs_pchero>君。\n ケイブへの スカウトの件について\n:
So, <cs_pchero>... You still haven't
told me your response about being scouted
into the Cave...

198694.「今の戦いで わかった。\n どうやら キミは 優しすぎるようだ。:
I've come to realize something from that
battle just now. It appears you harbor much
kindness.

198695.「その優しさゆえに 相手の命を絶つことを\n 無意識に 拒んでしまったのだ。:
And because of that kindness, you refused to
take the life of your enemy without a second
thought.

198696.「非情になり切れぬ者に エージェントの任務を\n 続けていくことは 難しい……。:
If an Agent cannot be ruthless in their ways,
then it is quite difficult for them to
complete their duties...

198697.「勝手な言い分と 思うだろうが\n 今回の話は なかったことにして もらいたい。:
You may think this as being unreasonable, but
I'd like to pretend this whole situation never
happened.

198698.「協力してもらった分の報酬は 渡そう。\n キミのはたらきには 感謝している。:
I will reward you for your assistance, as I
appreciate your efforts.

198699.「……<cs_pchero>君。\n エージェントには ならずとも\n キミの優:
<cs_pchero>...
Your kindness is capable of saving the world,
so I don't think you have to be an Agent.

198701.「すまないな。こうする決まりなのだ。:
I'm apologize. This is just the way it has to
be.

198702.「……ひとつ 言い忘れていた。\n 事後処理は ワガハイが やっておく。\n キ:
Just one last thing... I'll handle the rest.
You need not worry.

198703.「では さらばだ <cs_pchero>君。\n いずれまた 会うことも あるか:
Farewell, <cs_pchero>.
We may see each other again some day.

198705.「ちょっと 外に 出ていただけなのに\n いつの間に 中へ 入りやがった？:
I left for just a quick second, so when did
you come in here?

198706.「どうした？ 何か 探してるのか？\n ここには オレしか いねえし\n 金目の:
What's wrong? You lookin' for somethin'?
It's just me here. I don't got any money or
anything valuable, either.

198708.「なんだよ。言いたいことがあるなら 言えよ。\n 気持ち悪いじゃねえか。:
Huh? If you got somethin' to say, then just
spit it out. You're weirdin' me out.

198711.「……はぁ オレの息子ぉ？\n おいおい オレに 息子がいるように見えるか？:
Huh...? My son...? Do I look like the kinda
guy who's got a son?

198712.「こんな あこぎな商売 やってんだ。\n 息子どころか 嫁さんだって いやしねえ:
I run a shady business around here so havin'
a sonーlet alone a wifeーis outta the
question.

198713.「だいたい ここは パクレの野郎の家で\n オレの家じゃねえんだからな。\n 息:
This house belongs to Pakul, not me. Even if
I did have a son, I wouldn't be bringin' him
here.

198714.「まったく おかしなことを 言いやがるぜ。: You really are spoutin' a bunch of nonsense.

198715.どうやら ギャンドルは\nボンドルのことは 何も知らないようだ。:
It appears Gandor knows nothing about what
happened to Bondor.

198716.「……お前 ここんとこ パクレの野郎と\n よく ツルんでたみたいじゃねえか。\:
...You've been hangin' around that Pakul punk
a lot these days, right? I guess he must've
told you somethin'.

198717.「あいつの言葉を 真に受けちゃいけねえ。\n オレみたいに 振り回されるのがオチ:
Don't believe anythin' he says, or you'll end
up just like me...
